@@TJvPageScroller.HintColor
Summary
  Determines the color of the hint boxes for the Help Hints for the control.
Description
  Use HintColor to specify the hint box color. A default color value of clInfoBk is set for the
  HintColor property in the constructor when the application is created. To change the HintColor
  assign it a new TColor value.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPageScroller.OnMouseEnter
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves over the control.
Description
  Write an OnMouseEnter event handler to take specific action
  when the user moves the mouse over the control.
See Also
  OnMouseLeave
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPageScroller.OnMouseLeave
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves off the control.
Description
  Write an OnMouseLeave event handler to take specific action
  when the user moves the mouse off the control. For example,
  you can use this event to undo changes that were made in an
  OnMouseEnter event handler.
See Also
  OnMouseEnter
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPageScroller.OnParentColorChange
Summary
  Occurs when the color of the parent control changes.
Description
  Write an event handler for OnParentColorChange to take
  specific action when the color of the control's parent
  changes. For example, you can change the color of the control
  itself to match the parent's color even if the ParentColor
  property is false.
See Also
  Parent, ParentColor
